│ and mark it noreturn/memory(none), which is incorrect as the original         │
│ function returns 0 on some paths. Alive2 shows the transformation leads to UB │
│ via an inserted 'assume i1 0'.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug-only     │
│ logs show successive calls to TryToSimplifyUncondBranchFromEmptyBlock:        │
│ folding if.then, if.then1, if.then7 into 'e', then folding 'e' into           │
│ 'if.end2'. After this, the function becomes a one-block function with         │
│ 'unreachable'. This indicates an over-aggressive folding in                   │
│ TryToSimplifyUncondBranchFromEmptyBlock under CFG patterns where the          │
│ successor can reach the block being eliminated, creating a cycle or           │
│ contradiction that later passes turn into UB.\n\n3. Root Cause                │
│ Analysis:\nTryToSimplifyUncondBranchFromEmptyBlock assumes that merging an    │
│ empty BB into its successor is safe if PHIs can be redirected and certain     │
│ structural checks pass. However, it does not guard against cases where Succ   │
│ is (potentially) reachable from BB or vice versa in a way that creates or     │
│ exposes a problematic cycle when edges are rewired (especially after earlier  │
│ trivial block merges). In the reproducer, repeated merging collapses          │
│ control-flow such that an unreachable edge is introduced and later            │
│ canonicalized into 'assume false', causing UB. A conservative guard is needed │
│ to avoid merging when Succ can reach BB, which risks introducing              │
│ self-referential or cyclic constructs that break correctness in subsequent    │
│ analyses.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nWe add a conservative reachability   │
