│ The patch adds a conservative reachability guard to prevent problematic       │
│ empty-block merges that can create cycles and lead to miscompiles.            │
│                                                                               │
│ Summary of changes:                                                           │
│ - Include llvm/Analysis/CFG.h where needed to use isPotentiallyReachable.     │
│ - In TryToSimplifyUncondBranchFromEmptyBlock (Local.cpp), bail out early if   │
│ the successor can potentially reach the empty block. This prevents folding BB │
│ into Succ when doing so may introduce self-referential CFG patterns and       │
│ trigger incorrect downstream transformations.                                 │
│ - In SimplifyCFG’s simplifyUncondBranch, add the same reachability guard      │
│ before calling TryToSimplifyUncondBranchFromEmptyBlock.                       │
│                                                                               │
│ Files modified:                                                               │
│ - llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/Local.cpp                                         │
│   - Added #include "llvm/Analysis/CFG.h".                                     │
│   - Inserted:                                                                 │
│     - A reachability check: if (isPotentiallyReachable(Succ, BB)) return      │
│ false;                                                                        │
│ - llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyCFG.cpp                                   │
│   - Added #include "llvm/Analysis/CFG.h".                                     │
│   - Modified simplifyUncondBranch to include:                                 │
│     - !isPotentiallyReachable(Succ, BB) in the condition before trying to     │
│ simplify the empty block.                                                     │
│                                                                               │
│ This prevents the over-aggressive folding that led to the Alive2-reported UB  │
│ (noreturn memory(none) main with assume false), keeping the CFG semantics     │
│ intact in cases like the provided reproducer.                                 │
